    <p>
      A fourth form of symmetry involves reflecting points across the diagonal line <m>y=x</m>, where the <m>x</m>- and <m>y</m>-values are equal.
    </p>
    <p>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <p>
            <m>T(y,x)</m>: Symmetry about the line <m>y=x</m>. This is accomplished by interchanging the <m>x</m>- and <m>y</m>-values.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </p>
