    <p>
      Notice on the Unit Circle that the radius extending from the center at an angle of <m>30^{\circ}</m> to the point <m>T(x,y)=\left(\frac{1}{2},\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}\right)</m> is symmetric about the line <m>y=x</m>, in relation to the radius extending from the center at an angle of <m>60^{\circ}</m> to the point <m>P(x,y)</m>.
    </p>
