      Using symmetry about the <m>x</m>-axis, symmetry about the <m>y</m>-axis, and symmetry about the origin, we can complete the unit circle, as long as we remember that the <m>x</m>-values in Quadrants II and III are negative while the <m>y</m>-values in Quadrants III and IV are negative.
    </p>
