      Finally, we tie everything together and look at the entire Unit Circle. At first glance it may seem intimidating, however, similar to the Star Compass, there is a lot of symmetry (<m>x</m>-axis, <m>y</m>-axis, origin, about the line <m>y=x</m>) and it can help by focusing on one quadrant, and use symmetry to fill out the rest of the circle.
    </p>
